Philippines Stocks Movers: Belle, Manila Electric, MUSX Corp.

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-06-14T04:35:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/philippines-stocks-movers-belle-manila-electric-musx-corp-.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 0.8 percent to
4,140.27, heading for the lowest close since April 1.  Belle Corp. (BEL)  , a property and gaming company,
decreased for a 10th day, losing 2.3 percent to 4.75 pesos, the
longest losing streak since January 1990. The company said it
expects to raise between 4 billion pesos ($92 million) and 5
billion pesos from the sale of shares in a rights offer.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  , the country’s largest power
retailer, lost 0.7 percent to 276 pesos, snapping a five-day
rally that lifted it to a five-month high. Chief Operating
Officer Oscar Reyes said it may defer some projects after a
Philippine regulator ruling on its rates that’s “tough to live
by.” The company is reviewing the market for possible
fundraising, he said.  MUSX Corp. (MUSX)   declined for a fourth day, sliding 2.8
percent to 7 centavos, the longest losing streak since April 7.
The company’s board approved a plan to buy 51 percent of Total
Waste Management Recovery System Inc., a stock-exchange filing
showed. The company also plans to lend up to 25 million pesos to
Total Waste as additional working capital, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
